caption:
So I'm TRYING to have less of a sweet tooth these days. Trying. 🙊 It's NOT easy bc I love sugar. 🍫 Seriously, give me all the dessert! 🍪 These Key Lime Pie Energy Bites 💚 however are keeping me in check and are the perfect fix when I need something sweet. 👏🏼 Plus you only need 5️⃣ ingredients to make them! Check it:
-
▫️15 Medjool dates, pitted + soaked in water for 10 min
▫️1/2 cup raw almonds
▫️1 scoop protein powder of choice (try @bobsredmill!)
▫️3-4 tablespoons key lime juice
▫️1/2 teaspoon sea salt
-
Combine all the ingredients in a food processor and pulse until a dough-like mixture forms. Form into twelve 1-inch bites by hand. That's all folks! 🙃
cleaned_caption: So Im TRYING to have less of a sweet tooth these days Trying Its NOT easy bc I love sugar Seriously give me all the dessert These Key Lime Pie Energy Bites however are keeping me in check and are the perfect fix when I need something sweet Plus you only need 5️⃣ ingredients to make them Check it ▫️15 Medjool dates pitted soaked in water for 10 min ▫️12 cup raw almonds ▫️1 scoop protein powder of choice try bobsredmill ▫️34 tablespoons key lime juice ▫️12 teaspoon sea salt Combine all the ingredients in a food processor and pulse until a doughlike mixture forms Form into twelve 1inch bites by hand Thats all folks

caption:
Nachos are always the answer. -

These are one of my go to easy dinners!  It is simple and quick. It has lots of hidden veggies.  Most importantly, everyone cleans their plate on nacho night!  You can sub or add any veggies your family loves and load it up for a delicious weeknight meal.  If you want to lighten it up, try making the nachos on sweet mini peppers instead of chips! -

LOADED CHICKEN NACHOS -

Ingredients

1 bag tortilla chips

16 oz sharp cheddar cheese

1 can black beans, drained

1 can corn, drained

1 sweet bell pepper (any color)

2 cups shredded chicken

For topping:

guacamole

salsa

sour cream

cilantro, chopped

Instructions

1. Line a large sheet pan with foil.  Then spread the bag of chips over it as spread out as possible.

2. Sprinkle half the cheese over the nachos.  Then evenly top them with the black beans, corn, chopped pepper, and chicken.  Spread the remaining cheese over the top.

3. Place in an oven preheated to 425˚F and bake the nachos for 10-15 minutes or until they are heated through and the cheese on top is just starting to brown.

4. Remove from the oven and top with your choice of guacamole, salsa, sour cream, and fresh chopped cilantro.

5. Serve immediately - ENJOY!

Notes

These nachos can be made to be scaled to feed any number of people easily.  The amounts listed are suggestions based on what I usually use, but you can use more or less to taste. ©2017 The Pinning Mama - Recipe found at https://www.thepinningmama.com/baked-chicken-nachos - - - -

caption:
The best excuse to eat queso for dinner! - — Full Recipe Below— -

Being the good Texas born girl I am, I had to find a way to make cheese dip a main course, and so the queso chicken bake was born.  This brings all the cheesy goodness to the dinner table and the leftovers make a darn good filling for enchiladas later in the week. -

Tap the ribbon in the corner to save this recipe on IG or tap @easyfamilyrecipes to pin this recipe for later. -

Queso Chicken Bake

Ingredients

3-4 chicken breasts

1 can RO*TEL

1 can corn, drained

1 can black beans, drained and rinsed

16 oz Velvet

Instructions

1. Place the chicken breast in a baking dish flat. Butterfly breasts if they are especially thick.

2. Layer the corn, black beans, and RO*TEL on top of the chicken.

3. Dice the queso cheese into 1/2 inch cubes and spread them evenly over the top of the dish.

4. Cover the dish with foil and bake in a preheated oven at 375F for 45-55 minutes or until the chicken is done and the juices run clear. *if you want the cheese to be a little crispy remove the foil for the last 5 minutes of baking.

5. Remove from oven then remove the chicken breasts from the pan and use a fork or whisk to work the extra cheese into the juices to form more queso sauce.

6. Enjoy! Serve over rice, with chips, or with tortillas

For more tips and serving ideas, see the full post at: https://www.thepinningmama.com/one-dish-queso-chicken-bake-easy-dinner-recipe/ ©2016 The Pinning Mama - — - - -

caption:
This recipe is for the mushroom lover in your life! This is the EASIEST Chicken Marsala you will ever make.  Although it isn’t authentic, it delivers all the delicious flavor and will not disappoint. My husband even said it was his new favorite dinner! Seriously...You won’t believe how easy it makes this “fancy” dish! -

Easy Chicken Marsala -

Ingredients

1.5 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breast (about 3-4 chicken breasts), trimmed

3 cups baby bella mushrooms, sliced

1 can (10.5 oz) @Campbellskitchen cream of chicken soup

1/3 cup Marsala Cooking Wine

1 cup freshly grated parmesan cheese

1 tsp garlic powder

1/2 tsp salt

1/2 tsp pepper

Optional:

curly parsley for garnish

Instructions

1. Preheat the oven to 375˚F.

2. Lay the chicken breasts flat in a baking dish.  In a medium bowl, mix the mushrooms, soup, marsala wine, 1/2 cup parmesan cheese, garlic powder, salt, and pepper until combined then spread the mixture over the chicken breasts.  Top with remaining 1/2 cup of parmesan.

3. Bake on the middle rack for 25-35 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink (165˚F internal temp) then turn oven to broil for 2-4 minutes to brown the top and remove from oven.

4. Serve hot over mashed potatoes, pasta, or rice and enjoy!

For nutrition and serving suggestions, see the full post at: https://www.thepinningmama.com/easy-chicken-marsala/ ©2017 The Pinning Mama

caption:
Day 14!

MYTH:  Segregated special education programs are the only option for students with Down syndrome.

TRUTH: Students with Down syndrome are included in typical academic classrooms in schools across the country. The current trend in education is for full inclusion in social and educational settings. Sometimes students with Down syndrome are included in specific courses, while in other situations students are fully included in the typical classroom for all subjects. Increasingly, individuals with Down syndrome graduate from high school with diplomas, and participate in postsecondary academic and college programs. 
Inclusion works! ☀️

caption:
The end of Thanksgiving means one thing... COOKIES! -

Full Recipe Below! -

There are lots of snickerdoodle recipes out there.  What makes these really special is that they are extra thick and chewy.  I love when cookies are super thick and soft so you bite into them and have pillowy layers of delicious cinnamonny, buttery, flavor! -

Thick & Chewy Snickerdoodles

INGREDIENTS

1 cup butter, room temperature

1 1/4 cup sugar

1 egg

1 1/2 tsp vanilla extract

3 cups flour

1 1/2 tsp baking powder

1/4 tsp salt

1/4 cup sugar

1 1/2 tsp cinnamon

INSTRUCTIONS

1. In your @kitchenaid mixer cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Then add in egg and vanilla and mix until combined.

2. In a separate bowl combine dry ingredients - flour, baking powder and salt, and mix to combine.

3. Slowly add flour mixture to butter mixture, mixing well between each addition. The dough should not be sticky and should not be crumbly. If it is sticky, mix in flour one tablespoon at a time until it becomes not sticky. If the mixture is crumbly, mix in water one teaspoon at a time until the dough holds together.

4. Mix cinnamon and sugar together and place on a plate.

5. Measure dough with a 1/4 cup measure and roll into balls. Roll each ball to coat well in the cinnamon sugar mixture and place on a cookie sheet lined with a silpat liner or parchment paper and slightly flatten into a disc.

6. Bake at 350˚F for 12-15 minutes or until the center is just set. Let cool 2 minutes then cool on a wire rack.

Makes 12 large cookies.

Find more ideas at: https://www.thepinningmama.com/soft-chewy-snickerdoodle-cookies/

caption: The first step in becoming a better version of yourself is to envision it. Picture where you want to be in a month, year, 5 years, and 10 years. Make daily goals to get you to those milestone vision dates and do WHATEVER IT TAKES to get there. Sacrifices have to made and pain has to be endured. There's going to be days where you feel better than others and it's those days that you push past your "feelings" and get done what needs to get done that make all the difference. Listen; NO ONE OWES YOU ANYTHING. If you want something, you have to work for it. I take enormous pride in my physique because I know it can't be bought or given. It has to be earned. 179lbs on the left and 191lbs on the right. 12 quality pounds of growth in 4 months. It wasn't from steroids. It wasn't from all this bullshit supplement craze. It was from squatting till I passed out, bench pressing till my training partner had to pry the bar off me, and deadlifting till I puked. caption:
Hi friends!  I'm still loving this bold black wall, and I plan to paint the rest of the room white eventually.  Hopefully sooner rather than later.  But on a day like today, I cannot help but be grateful for all those who sacrificed so much so that you and I can enjoy the freedom we do.  I stood in the check out line at Lowes the other day and watched countless people walk by an elderly veteran who was collecting money for the VFW on their way out.  They neither donated money or so much as said Hello or Thank you.  I had my 4 year old daughter with me and I believe it is my duty to teach her that we show appreciation to those who've sacrificed for our freedom.  So we walked over, I handed my daughter a few dollars to put in the donation bin, and I thanked that elderly veteran for his service.  We must must must set an example for our children.  To teach them gratitude, kindness, and generosity.  May we not forget that while we are picking out paint colors at Lowes, that  there are brave men and women out there fighting for our freedom and protection.  And may that not be lost on this next generation that we are raising ❤💙
.
.
.
.
.

caption:
There is nothing better (or faster) than this soup on a cold day🍂🍁🌨 - — FULL RECIPE BELOW— -

This soup has been a long time friend of mine.  We revisit every winter and I remember how much I love this old friend.  When you look at the recipe, you think… hmmm maybe?  But I promise you if you love the flavors of rich chicken with a hint of fresh lemon this will soon be one of your new best friends too. -

Save this recipe with the ribbon in the corner or tap @easyfamilyrecipes to pin it for later. -

10 Minute Lemon Chicken Soup -

Ingredients

2 (10.5 ounce) can condensed chicken and rice soup

2 (10.75 ounce) can condensed cream of chicken soup, undiluted - I use the low fat kind but both work great

5 cups chicken broth

1 rotisserie chicken, meat removed and diced

3 tablespoons lemon juice - I prefer fresh

Salt & Pepper to taste

Instructions

1. In a large pot combine and mix the two canned soups together

2. Add the chicken broth and use a whisk to combine the broth into the creamy mixture.

3. Stir in the chicken meat and lemon juice and season with salt and pepper to taste.

4. Cook over medium heat until the edges bubble and the soup is heated through.

5. Serve warm and garnish with parsley if desired.

caption:
All those things that sound fancy.  They really aren’t that hard.  Take Roasted Garlic for example.  Call a dish garlic pasta and it is plain, call it roasted garlic pasta and it is instant fancy.  Mashed Potatoes… Roasted Garlic Mashed Potatoes. See?! The secret though… Roasted Garlic is SO EASY to make!  Try it then keep it on hand to season pasta, bread, potatoes, etc.

Super Easy Roasted Garlic

Ingredients

2 cup garlic
1 tablespoon olive oil
Salt & pepper to taste

Instructions

Lay a sheet of heavy duty aluminum foil flat.Put garlic in the middle of the foil.Drizzle with olive oil, then season with salt and pepper.fold the foil up to make a pouch where the seam side is on the top.Place the pouch on a cookie sheet and bake at 400F for 25-35 minutes or until the garlic is tender and is starting to brown.

Notes

Recipe can be doubled or tripled but may require extra cooking time.Store in the refrigerator in an air tight container to keep as a seasoning on hand.

caption:
Mashed Potatoes on #Thanksgiving? Yay or Nay? -

This Garlic Parmesan Mashed Potatoes recipe is a winner not only because it is delicious, but also because it is made in the #crockpot so you can free up the stovetop for other things and let the #slowcooker do the work on these mashed potatoes while you get everything else done! -

CROCK POT GARLIC PARMESAN MASHED POTATOES -

Ingredients

5 lbs red potatoes

1 cup chicken broth

3 cloves garlic

1/2 cup butter

1 1/2 cup sour cream

1 cup grated parmesan

1 tsp salt

2 tbsp oregano

Instructions

1.Please note this makes a HUGE amount

2. Wash and cut your potatoes into quarters

3. Place in the slow cooker with broth, garlic, and butter and cook on low 6-8 hours

4. Potatoes should be easily pierced with a fork when done.

5. Add sour cream, parmesan, salt and oregano.

6. Use a potato masher to mash and blend until well combined and the potatoes are the desired consistency.

7. Serve or keep warm in crock pot until time to serve.

For tips and tricks on this recipe and serving suggestions, see the full post at:

caption:
Have you ever made cranberry sauce from scratch?  It is SO EASY you will give up the canned stuff forever!- — Full Recipe Below— -

Cranberry sauce is one of my absolute favorite parts of Thanksgiving dinner and this recipe is my go to!  There are only 3 ingredients and you can even make it a few days in advance to keep things less hectic on the day. -

Use the ribbon in the corner to save this post, or tap @easyfamilyrecipes to pin it for later. -

3 INGREDIENT CRANBERRY SAUCE -

Ingredients

12 oz cranberries

1 cup orange juice

1/2 - 1 cup white sugar

Use sugar amount based on preferred sweetness:

1/2 cup for more tart cranberry sauce

1 cup for sweet cranberry sauce

3/4 cup for mildly sweet cranberry sauce

Instructions

1. Combine cranberries, orange juice and sugar (amount based on your sweetness preference) in a sauce pan over medium-high heat and cook stirring frequently until the mixture begins to boil.2. Once the mixture boils, reduce the heat to low and continue to cook for 3-5 additional minutes, or until it is the "chunkiness" you desire.  The longer you cook the more smooth it will be.3. Remove from heat and cool in fridge until serving.  Cranberry sauce will thicken as it cools.4. Serve chilled and ENJOY!

Notes

You can make this up to 1 week ahead of time and store in an airtight container until you are ready to use. . . . .. . .

caption:
Pretty sure dad would LOVE these Bacon Wrapped Sweet Potato Fries for #FathersDay! 😍🍴✨ Super easy to do - here's how you make it happen:
-
1️⃣ Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Cut sweet potatoes into fries. 
2️⃣ Place them in a bowl, season with black pepper and smoked paprika, and toss. Wrap each fry with one slice of uncooked bacon and place on lined baking sheet. 
3️⃣ Bake until sweet potatoes are tender and bacon is crispy, about 30 to 35 minutes. Serve with your favorite dipping sauce.
-
P.S. The sauce in the picture is a Chipotle Aioli Sauce that I quickly whipped up using mayo, minced garlic, lime juice, and chili powder. 🙌🏼
